@kilaueabart - SYZYGY is one of my favorite words and, although I don't think I'd heard it used in the context of this clue, I knew what it meant right away. 

I first learned SYZYGY as an undergrad in invertebrate biology class. The sutures that join the skeletal elements in crinoids are called SYZYGies. I leared its astronomical meaning later on. I think the more general meaning might derive from those more specific usages, but I do not know for sure. I'm sure David Connell could let us know. 

I love when I learn new things about words I already knew -- almost as much as I love learning words that appear in a crossword that I have never known before.

